---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import siteConfig from '../site.config.ts';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Image Tools"
  description="Image Tools provides free, browser-based image compression, resizing, and conversion tools. 100% private — your images never leave your device."
  canonical={`${siteConfig.domain}/about`}
>
  <SiteNav currentPath="/about" />

  <main class="page-main">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About Image Tools</h1>

      <p>
        Image Tools is a free collection of browser-based image utilities built for everyday tasks: compressing photos for government exam applications, resizing images to passport or e-commerce dimensions, and converting between JPEG, PNG, and WebP formats.
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy-first by design</h2>
      <p>
        Every tool on this site runs entirely in your browser using the HTML5 Canvas API. When you upload an image, it is loaded directly into your browser's memory — it is never transmitted to any server, never stored in a database, and never seen by anyone other than you. This is not a policy promise; it is a technical fact. There is no server-side image processing code because there is no server involved at all.
      </p>
      <p>
        This design also means the tools work fast — there is no upload wait time, no queue, and no rate limit. Processing happens instantly on your own device, using your own CPU and memory. Once the page is loaded, the tools continue to work even if your internet connection drops.
      </p>

      <h2>Who is this for?</h2>
      <p>
        Image Tools was built with Indian students, job seekers, and professionals in mind. Government exam portals (SSC, UPSC, NTA, IBPS, RRB) impose strict requirements on photo and signature file sizes and dimensions. Getting these wrong causes application rejections. Our tools are specifically pre-configured for these common requirements — 20 KB, 50 KB, 100 KB compress targets; 276×118 px SSC signature; 413×531 px passport photo — so you get the right output without needing to know the technical details.
      </p>
      <p>
        Web developers and e-commerce sellers also benefit from the format conversion and compression tools. Converting product images from PNG to WebP or JPEG, compressing images to under 100 KB for faster page loads, and resizing to standard e-commerce dimensions (600×600 px) are all tasks this site handles well.
      </p>

      <h2>Free forever</h2>
      <p>
        All tools are completely free to use with no account, no sign-up, and no usage limits. The site is supported by display advertising. If you find the tools useful, the best way to support the project is to share it with someone who needs it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-main {
    padding: 3rem 0 6rem;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: 1.5rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--site-text);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--site-text);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.5rem;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--site-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    max-width: 65ch;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
</style>
